phrs.translation: n. 领主之宅邸；庄园主的住宅

sentences.sentence: It was the quintessence of an English manor house.
sentences.translation: 那是典型的英式庄园宅第。

sentences.sentence: On this occasion he was away from Misselthwaite Manor until afternoon.
sentences.translation: 这次，他一直拖到下午，才到米塞斯维特庄园。

sentences.sentence: We've got to drive five miles across Missel Moor before we get to the Manor.
sentences.translation: 我们得行五英里跨过米索荒原后才能到庄园。
